This paper deals with a problem in computer vision, specifically in estimating fundamental matrices. The proposed solution involves the use of neural network architectures, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of performance using various metrics, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of the KITTI dataset suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.MM.
